item.description:
Problem Statement The $n$-th term of the sequence of triangle numbers is given by \(t_n = \frac{n(n+1)}{2}\); so the first ten triangle numbers are
\begin{equation*} 1,3,6,10,15,21,28,36,45,55,\ldots \end{equation*}
By converting each letter in a word to a number corresponding to its alphabetical position and adding these values we form a word value. For example, the word value for SKY is \(19 + 11 + 25 = 55 = t_{10}\). You are given a file words.

Problem Statement The sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers is
\begin{equation*} 1^2 + 2^2 + \cdots + 10^2 = 385. \end{equation*}
The square of the sum of the first ten natural numbers is
\begin{equation*} (1 + 2 + \cdots + 10)^2 = 55^2 = 3025 \end{equation*}
Hence the difference between the sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers and the square of the sum is \(3025 - 385 = 2640\).
